officers and the American officers. Were there

30:23.216 --> 30:28.522
any times that there was tension? Never. As a 
matter of fact, working with the Royal Canadian

30:29.203 --> 30:34.810
Air Force types was just like working with 
America. No problem, as a matter of fact. I can't

30:37.381 --> 30:52.503
think of any problem, ever any problem, either at 
the planning stage and in Ottawa and Washington

30:37.381 --> 30:52.503
D.C. at the high level stages where we even sat down 
in some cases with, you know, political

30:37.381 --> 30:52.503
civilians, high level civilians, State 
Department types. Never any. It was, for

30:56.869 --> 31:03.439
instance, compared to the problem I had in Russia 
dealing with people, no problem whatsoever. And

31:04.347 --> 31:10.793
subsequent dealings with the Italians and NATO, 
never. It's just like planning with Americans. No

31:15.457 --> 31:17.479
problem whatsoever. And subsequently in the 
field when I had command of radar divisions and

31:17.499 --> 31:24.666
fighter squadrons, the corporation was 
splendid. They're terrific bunch. What about the

31:27.028 --> 31:30.131
quality of the Air Force officers? Canada? Great. 
Terrific. On our quality? Oh, yeah. Terrific.

31:38.873 --> 31:39.734
See, they were smaller. Sure. And I don't know if 
that makes for them being as good or better, but

31:41.075 --> 31:52.268
they had the cream of the crop of Canada, young men. 
