33:01.510 --> 33:03.653
the basic concept of that? Air defense controlled 
by computer. Oh, the SAGE. SAGE, S-A-G-E,

33:07.218 --> 33:30.150
standing for Semi-Automatic Ground Environment 
System, where a controller at a normal radar site

33:07.218 --> 33:30.150
looking at the scope and seeing the blips of an 
incoming bomber would speak over a ground-to-air

33:07.218 --> 33:30.150
communication radio telephone, RT, and direct a 
pilot across the scope, seeing him pit-blip also

33:30.451 --> 33:37.339
where he'd make the intercept. Semi-automatic 
ground environment was of a nature where

33:39.781 --> 33:54.638
eventually we didn't even plan to have data link 
and actually tied into the flight control system

33:39.781 --> 33:54.638
of the airplane where a man wasn't even in the link. 
Everything was done automatically by computer

33:54.718 --> 33:59.243
until the two blips came together on a scope. It's 
automatically telling the fire control system

33:59.678 --> 34:04.686
and the all-weather fighter when to fire the 
missile. That was the ultimate. In some cases, we

